After another turn in the convoluted explanations of Brian Molefe’s resignation-not-resignation or retirement-not-retirement from Eskom, Molefe himself appeared bewildered, asking the evidence leader in the parliamentary inquiry into the power utility whether it was being implied he’d written two resignation letters. Advocate Ntuthuzelo Vanara coolly replied: “We are trying to get ourselves out of the mist.” That might be a good rejoinder to any of those being grilled by Parliament, or at least those (and it does seem to be many) who react badly to being questioned in this way.
 
